description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a well organised, articulate, highly motivated and experienced Data Quality Support Analyst who would like to work in our Physical Health Service? If so, this role could be for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a data analyst who can produce good quality and well-presented reports and audits from SystmOne and other databases for managers, the wider Senior Leadership Team in Solent NHS and Commissioners. You will also be expected to keep SystmOne and other databases up to date with continuous housekeeping and cleansing. Reporting on anomalies within these databases is also a key function of this role. Therefore, having a meticulous eye and paying attention to detail and the ability to have focussed attention for long periods is paramount. Confidentiality is of utmost importance and should be adhered to at all times. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Also, the successful applicant will:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be able to use own initiative and apply a commonsense approach to problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be curious and have an enquiring mind&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;have strong communication skills with the ability to communicate effectively at all levels&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be organised, able to multi-task and work under pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be team spirited and also able to work autonomously&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;be conscientious and have excellent prioritisation skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are looking for a new challenge and can demonstrate your suitability for this role, then we look forward to hearing from you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is part-time, 22.5 hours per week and will be based at the Adelaide Health Centre in Millbrook.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the attached job description and person specification for more details and should you wish to discuss the role further please contact Diana Harrison on 07795 451 647.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that should this post attract sufficient interest, we may choose to close at an earlier date. We strongly suggest that you apply at an early stage.&lt;strong&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date of this post, please presume that you have not been selected.&lt;/strong&gt;Candidates selected for interview will be contacted within 2-3 weeks; therefore you should check your emails regularly including junk mail folders.&lt;/p&gt;
